**Moving the AQS breadboard setup to the PCB board**

After completing the assembly of the AQS on the breadboard (the guide can be found in **Assembly**) we can transfer components onto the PCB board. 

![alt text](../images/Design-and-Assembly-of-PCB1.png)

The steps for this are to:

1. Download the CSL\_AQS\_V5 project from our Github   
   ![alt text](../images/Design-and-Assembly-of-PCB2.png)  
     
2. Use KiCad to download the Gerber and Drill files of the PCB board   
   1. Open KiCad → File → Open Project

![alt text](../images/Design-and-Assembly-of-PCB3.png)

2. Select CSL\_AQS\_V1.kicad\_pcb → File → Fabrication Outputs → Gerbers 

![alt text](../images/Design-and-Assembly-of-PCB4.png)

3. Select Plot and Generate Drill files (To easily access these files creating a new folder is suggested)   
     
3. Order the PCB through a PCB manufacturer 

( Note. The Gerber and Drill files are needed to order the PCB board)

4. Assemble Sensors according to the labeled components and connections
